The Prague Stock Exchange ended with fewer points at the end of the day
After the rapid fall of the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange corrected its losses.
Transactions of <0xC4><0x8C>EZ shares reached about half the value they have on a normal day.
The Prague Stock Exchange, at the beginning of trading Tuesday, reacted immediately to Monday’s fall when it fell about 6%.
The downturn this time is due to the fall in stocks on Wall Street.
Also here is expressed the market reaction to the result of the vote of the American Assembly of Representatives who refused to support the plan of stabilization of the secretary of the financial sector.
Fall of shares in Asia
Asian stocks saw a dramatic fall on Tuesday, though the index eventually softened some of the losses throughout the day.
The Hong Kong Hang Seng Stock Exchange index during its financial day was nearly four percent, although it later mitigated its losses by reducing the decline by almost 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index that tracks Chinese stock movements on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange fell 3.8 percent, in Shanghai the markets were closed.
Stocks on the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent but, in the end, the losses fell to 4.3 percent.
Taiwan’s stock market, according to the Index’s secretary, fell 3.6 percent.
"The planned rescue actions in the U.S. are unsafe and this influences the financial markets around the world," said Hong Kong Currency Office Chief Joseph Yam.
Although Hong Kong is a part of China, it alone determines its monetary policy, that is, without dependence on the Central Bank of China.
Interest rates in Hong Kong are at the same level as those in the United States.
U.S. lawmakers should meet again as soon as possible, according to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, and approve a proposal to support the financial system.
Otherwise, it threatens that the falls will be felt in other countries.
Bloody bath of American stocks
On Monday, the American Assembly of Representatives rejected the plan to help the financial system to which 700 billion dollars (almost 12 trillion kroner) should be devoted.
Lawmakers thus ignored President George Bush’s invitation to support his plan.
For Bush, the plan would address the root causes of the financial crisis and help stabilize the entire economy.
On Monday, U.S. stocks experienced a bloody bath and mainly the stock index picked up the biggest drop in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones index fell to nearly seven percent, a similar fall in volume last recorded in 1987.
The index went down before it was announced but as soon as it was shown that the assembly proposal did not go forward, the index began to fall freely.
Congress Withdraws: U.S. Government Can Inject $700 Billion into Banking
The highest representatives of Congress and the government, President George W. Bush, agreed on a comprehensive pact of financial aid to the American financial system.
The vote will take place early next week.
U.S. lawmakers sparked a breach in talks on approving the bailout in its form of aid to the U.S. financial system in the amount of $700 billion (approximately 12 trillion kroner).
However, it is not yet won.
Congressmen must fine-tune some details of the contract before they can make the final form of the law public and vote on it.
The plan to help the financial system will be discussed Monday at the Assembly of Representatives.
Barney Frank, chairman of the Committee on Financial Services and Assembly Banking, told Reuters on Sunday.
According to some sources, the vote on the plan could be held in the Senate not before Wednesday.
According to economists, the arrival of the ratification of the bailout plan should represent the announcement of a first psychologically significant factor for the revitalization of the financial market.
Later, however, "disenchantment" will be achieved thanks to the complex mechanisms whose help to the market will also reach in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
“We have made a big step forward.
We resolved our differing views regarding the way the market stabilization package should be," Democrat Nancy Pelosia told Bloomberg.
According to her, the final vote could still take place on Sunday.
Representatives from lawmakers met Sunday night with Finance Minister Henry Paulson to give a definitive form to the government fund.
It should buy from financial corporations the unsold mortgage assets that lead financial firms to hard losses and threaten the stability of the entire system.
“We are about to close the agreement on the plan, which will work and must also be effective in the market.
We still need to continue with the sanitation plan, but I think we’re already on it,” Paulson said.
A Sign for Asian Business
The global financial crisis has an express impact on the rapidly falling stock market.
According to Democratic Sen. for Nevada Harry Reid, lawmakers are doing everything they can to get Congress to definitively pass a deal on Sunday.
They want to reassure investors’ business in the Asian financial market as these are the ones that are in the first time zone and where Congress could influence Monday’s trade.
However, for now there is nothing clear for sure about when the two chambers of the American Congress will vote and, even, if they will not stagnate at the last moment with some problem.
Lawmakers believe it will be approved in the coming days.
The law, however, will undergo a number of changes.
The total amount intended to help the system should be divided into two parts.
The first 350 billion must be available as soon as possible, as President George Bush requested.
However, Congress can block the release of the remaining amount if it has the impression that the program does not fulfill its function, which would be another $100 billion and, later, the last $350 billion.
Bush praised the progress of the meetings
On the other hand, the president can veto this decision but Congress can overcome its veto by a majority of votes.
Despite these changes, the basic idea of the program was preserved, which consisted of earning financial resources for the repurchase of bad mortgage securities whose value fell because hundreds of thousands of Americans are not able to finish paying their mortgages.
“We worked everything.
The House of Representatives should be ready to vote on the bill on Sunday, and the Senate on Monday," said Republican Sen. Judd Gregg.
President Bush is also pleased with the progress of the meetings.
His spokesman, Tony Fratto, announced that Bush is pleased with Saturday’s progress and that he values “the efforts of both sides to stabilize our financial market and protect our economy.”
Limitation of the armored contract
Senate Banking Committee Chairman Christopher Dodd, chief negotiator, said lawmakers decided on the responsibility of the taxpayer tax protection program money for its losses, a relieving closure of the planned finance plan.
The new law should also limit so-called armored contracts for directors of companies participating in the program, and create a committee that will have control of the Fund.
This should be handled by the Ministry of Finance.
“We’ve worked very hard on it, and we’ve made a big step toward the agreement that will work and that will be effective for the market and for all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also includes helping homeowners who are having trouble with their payments.
The government would have to agree on new payments on the mortgages it buys in order to lower the monthly charges on debtors’ installment payments and enable them to stay with their homes.
Marek: psychological help
The proposed plan is, according to the chief economist of Patria Finance, David Marek, a good idea that will be realized but rather difficult.
“And this is why it is not known with what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets will be bought.
This will be decisive for the sharing of losses between the financial sector and the government," Marek said this week, for the iHNed.cz server.
Whether the plan is approved now or early next week is not, according to Marek, so relevant.
"Much more importantly, as early as this week, the congressmen will agree on their support and give them their approval as soon as possible.
This important and psychological agreement that such approval will be reached is, at this time, the most important thing," Marek said.
Armed fighting: the MP3 player against the mobile.
We advise you how to choose
While almost every mobile phone plays MP3 files, no MP3 player can make calls.
It is better to buy only the phone.
Still, there are enough reasons for man to acquire only the breeder.
The choice depends practically on the manner of its use and the demands of the future owner.
It will probably be difficult for him to acquire the most modern turntable to listen on it the latest album of Maxim Turbulenc.
On the other hand, this type of music products such as LP records no longer come out, and as far as their quality is concerned, there is not a single objective reason to continue buying them.
If vinyl records with art rock, jazz or blues music are crowded on their shelves, you are probably dreaming, at least, of this type of turntable.
This is the same with music that is on the way, i.e. compressed, simplified music - MP3 music.
And here there are price and quality categories.
For some it may be unacceptable to spend eight thousand crowns on a player, the same as for a Pink Floyd lover who will hardly try the market helmets of twenty crowns.
