And music playback is one of the biggest energy tragons.
Few mobile phones are able to play music for more than ten or twelve hours, most of them much less.
In this sense, music players (especially the simplest ones) clearly have a higher performance.
Therefore, keep in mind that cheap mobiles will not play for more than two hours.
If in addition to this, on top, constantly call still get, for more security, a charger for work - this applies also to the most expensive appliances.
With the MP3 player this problem will not have it, because even the worst ones can withstand at least 9 hours of uninterrupted operation after a charge.
Another problem happens when recording music on the mobile.
Unfortunately, only a part of the devices have the universal USB connector and not all of them can be connected directly to the computer without special software.
