Unfortunately the offer of the operators is miserable and the majority is limited only to the themes of fleeting radio success.
The prices are also not the lowest.
However, in general, it is assumed that precisely this way of selling music (whether by GSM, internet or wireless internet) in the future will dominate the music industry.
Most people always carry a mobile phone.
Whenever you want to hear something, you will find the phone in your pocket, while the MP3 player will be forgotten at home.
However, it still depends on whether you always carry headphones or at least handsfree.
If not, you can use a built-in player that has virtually every mobile even if it is at least one MP3 player.
